items.text:
Hi everyone,
I‚Äôm Callum Foley 24, an actor based in Nottingham. I‚Äôve recently been working on background and student film projects, and I‚Äôm keen to get involved in short films, indie projects, and commercials to build on-screen experience.

I‚Äôm currently training at Nottingham Actors Workshop and working towards joining **Spotlight**, so I‚Äôm looking to create footage that will form my first professional showreel.

I have professional headshots available and would be happy to send them over if you have a role I could be suitable for. I‚Äôm based in Nottingham but happy to travel for projects.

You can reach me at **callumfoley1000@gmail.com**.

Thanks,

items.text:
Hey guys, I'm running a taster session for the screen acting class this Friday for only a fiver! 

In the session, you'll get to practice on a given scene over a couple of takes and I'll also go through the three programs of this autumn: 
* Screen acting drop-in 
* Screen acting Monthly workshop (over 4weeks) to develop presence and get confident on camera. 
* The directing actors Workshop with the last monday of each month with actors in the room! 
* More info at interactors.co.uk @ : info.interactors@gmail.com Make sure you book the ticket for friday via the website if you wish to come! Looking forward to seeing you there!  whttps://www.instagram.com/p/DOeaxfCDLI_/?igsh=MWU0ZHg5aGh5cmI0OQ==

items.text:
Thought I‚Äôd introduce myself, although Im new to the page, I am not new to the industry.

Im Pete.
I‚Äôm an Assistant Director (Film) and Sound recordist (MA and BA hons in sound production for TV and film).
I started off my career in the industry at the age of 12/13 years old. As an extra in a feature film franchise. Again at 16 and another at 19 years old.
Inbetween those times, I trained as a theatre actor, appeared in a few short films, music videos and made my theatre Debut as a Director with christmas Panto‚Äôs.
During my 20‚Äôs I toured Europe as a musician and clown for a circus company. inbetween tours, Iappeared twice in London‚Äôs West End and performed at the London 2012 olympic opening ceremony.
In 2016 I began writing my own short films and a feature film, which is currently in talks with Channel 4 and the BFI.
2019, I decided to go to University to study TV and film production and ended up specialising in Sound production.

I know it‚Äôs not you‚Äôre usual kind of post. I see a lot of new/young talent asking for advice, hints and tips for navigating the industry. 
If anybody wants/needs advice, I‚Äôm happy to help where I can.

‚ÄúAdvice is a form of nostalgia, dispensing it is a way of fishing the past.‚Äù- Baz Luhrmann.

Vi leder efter en skandinavisk mand og kvinde i slut 30‚Äôerne/start 40‚Äôerne samt en pige p√• 7‚Äì8 √•r til en varm og trov√¶rdig reklameproduktion for en detailk√¶de. Gerne s√∏ges som en samlet familie, men ikke n√∏dvendigt 

üìç Optagelse: cirka 4 timer 
Lokation: Herning  
üìÖ Dato: 7 oktober 
üé• Brug: Sociale medier, TV, biograf og online i Danmark, Sverige, Norge og Finland
üñºÔ∏è Stillbilleder: Bruges online og evt. p√• print i k√¶dens fysiske butikker
‚è≥ Brugsret: 3 √•r med mulighed for forl√¶ngelse (brugen af reklamen er dog s√¶son pr√¶get, s√• ville i vinterm√•nederne) 

Udstr√•ling: Glad og frisk udstr√•ling, og med evnen til at skabehygge.
Samspillet mellem de to voksne og datteren er b√¶rende, og det er derfor vigtigt at de voksne er gode med b√∏rn og at barnet er skuespils vant.

üì¢Volunteers Wanted - Videographers! Liverpool Mystery Eventüì¢

CAJ Productions is looking for 2 more reliable volunteers to help with a one-off mystery stunt in Liverpool City Centre on Saturday 20th September 2025.

It's part of a brand-new UK theatre tour coming in 2026, and this will be one of our headline public marketing stunts. 

The role is simple, but really important:

. Filming the event (reactions) on a phone (2 people required)

What you'll get:

. Travel expenses covered

. Be part of an unusual, exciting event that's going to get a lot of attention

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

items.text: Shailene Woodley (‚ÄûBig Little Lies‚Äú): ‚ÄúI think Tony is absolutely incredible and coming to class for me isn‚Äôt just about letting loose and growing my ability as an actor but more sometimes to really open up myself to the universe and just be. Sometimes I find him saying things that I mentally live by and its so refreshing to constantly hear them being affirmed. Thank you so much for every week re-instilling that positivity and creativity and openness within. You allow me as an actor to forget about the character and remember about Shailene, which makes every movement, moment and word so authentic and true. I‚Äôm so grateful to have you as a mentor.‚Äù

items.text:
Hi everyone! I‚Äôm an attorney exploring a career pivot into the entertainment industry, and I‚Äôd love to connect with those working for TV/film studios, music companies, talent agencies, or management firms. I‚Äôm not looking to pitch anything or expecting a job offer, just hoping to have a few honest, informational conversations as I figure out what path might be the right fit for me.

If you're open to sharing your experience or offering a bit of insight, I‚Äôd really appreciate it!!

Thanks so much in advance

items.text:
INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

BACKGROUND MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

*Join us at the Hive Creative Space: Monthly Creative Networking/Gathering*

Join us on Sunday 28th September at Wolverhampton Art Gallery, between 1-4pm for an inspiring session of short film screenings, creative talks, networking, workshops, games and collaboration.

There will also be a showcase of two short films:

SOFT - directed by Scott Driver

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

BACKGROUND MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

Mit navn er Luca Giusio 
Jeg er 17 √•r 
Og bor i Kolding/vejle 

Jeg laver lige det her opslag fordi jeg rigtig gerne vil v√¶re skuespiller og elsker det med film og skuespil og alt i den dur 
Jeg er en passioneret og energisk person, der elsker at udtrykke mig gennem b√•de drama og humor. 

Jeg har erfaring med:

Har v√¶ret en del af dystopia i Vejle siden 2020
Har g√•et til teater i 2 √•r og v√¶ret med i 2 forestillinger 
Har lavet sm√• kortfilm og min egen spillefilm igennem min barndom 

H√∏jde: 175
Sprog: Dansk/engelsk 
Jeg er dedikeret l√¶renem ‚Äì og s√• elsker jeg at arbejde kreativt sammen med andre

jeg h√•ber at h√∏re fra jer

Hi! :) I just wanted to quickly introduce myself- My name is giana, im an actress, production assistant (PA) and Assistant Stage Manager (ASM). I've been working on sets/ doing set construction since I was 14 years old, among doing other things like handling props and working on the fly system.  I just recently got into acting at the beginning of July so I don't have a ton of acting experience (yet) since I just started but I have been in 2 films so far- one movie and one short film. I would love to gain more experience as an actress but I do still want to work behind the scenes as well. 

 If you have any questions or want to reach out feel free to comment them or DM me, Thank you!

items.text:
**Paid Studio Gig ‚Äì Surrey, BC (1‚Äì2 days, max 7 hrs/day)**

Hey Vancouver actors! We‚Äôre producing a batch of short videos for our brand (YouTube, Reels, TikTok, Facebook) and are looking for a confident on-camera presenter to record with us at our Surrey studio.

**What it is:**
* 1‚Äì2 studio days, max **7 hours per day**
* Scripted teleprompter reads + a few simple pickups/B-roll
* We provide the studio, teleprompter, and all gear
* **Contract provided** and **payment in full on wrap**

**You:** Comfortable on camera, friendly, clear delivery, can self-report to Surrey.

**Dates/Rate:** negotiable and flexable 

If you‚Äôre interested, please fill out this form, https://form.jotform.com/252610493666057 

with:
* Headshot + reel/links
* Your availability in **[date range]**
* A quick note confirming you can get to Surrey

Thanks! Excited to meet some local talent.

**CASTING CALL "Migraine" - BACKGROUND**

*What if you uncovered something dark buried in a past life?*

Migraine is a psychological-spiritual thriller short film, and we are currently casting background for a **1950s jazz club scene.**

**Details:**
* Age: **19+**
* Gender: **Any **
* Ethnicity:** Any** 
* Location: **Greater Vancouver Area** 
* Rate:** Volunteer. We are a low-budget indie film hyper-focused on quality.** 
* Date: **Sept. 25 or 28**

*please let us know if you available for one or both dates

To submit please send us your name and contact info at **migraine.shortfilm@gmail.com**

We look forward to working with you!

‚ÄºÔ∏èNORTHWEST BIPOC ENTERTAINERS‚ÄºÔ∏è

We are actively seeking talented BIPOC performers to bring beloved characters such as; Princess Tiana, Mulan, Mirabel, Jasmine, Moana, iconic Korean figures and more to life through engaging and authentic performances.

To our company representation matters! We are committed to celebrating the rich cultural heritage of these characters embodied by casting performers who reflect their backgrounds. Whether you're an experienced entertainer or a passionate newcomer, if you have a love for storytelling, performance, and creating magical moments for audiences of all ages, we invite you to join us in inspiring the next generation through inclusive and empowering portrayals.

Please PM Ever Enchanted Events or email everenchantedevent@gmail.com with a headshot, CV and a little about yourself and your backgroundü•∞‚≠êÔ∏è

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

Well thanks having us at the Folkestone Fringe this year!

Drehort: LEIPZIG

Drehtag: 26.09.2025 - 10.00 Uhr

Geplanter Drehzeitraum: halber Drehtag (4‚Äì5 Stunden)
Schauspielhonorar: 500 ‚Ç¨ pauschal

Was wir drehen:

F√ºr unseren Kunden, einen Immobilienunternehmen aus LEIPZIG, produzieren wir 25 kurze UGC-Videos (User Generated Content) f√ºr Social Media & Online-Ads. Die Videos sind authentisch gesprochene Clips, die direkt in die Kamera eingesprochen werden ‚Äì klar, sympathisch, ruhig.

Skriptl√§nge pro Video: 40‚Äì60 Sekunden, ein Teleprompter ist vor Ort ‚Äì keine Auswendiglernerei notwendig.

Gesucht werden:
* 1 Schauspielerin & 1 Schauspieler
* Alter: 28‚Äì40 Jahre
* Look: authentisch, gepflegt, urban-professionell ‚Äì ein nat√ºrlicher ‚ÄûYoung Professional‚Äú-Vibe (Think: Start-up, Immobilienberater, Creator mit Vertrauensausstrahlung)
* Sprache: Hochdeutsch, sichere Sprechweise, gute Artikulation
* Erfahrung mit Kamera & Social Media Ads von Vorteil, aber keine Voraussetzung

√úber uns:

Wir sind die IMMO 4.0 GmbH, ein Performance-Marketing-Unternehmen aus Heidelberg.

Wir entwickeln Marketingkampagnen f√ºr Immobilienvertriebe, Bautr√§ger und Kapitalanlageprodukte im DACH-Raum ‚Äì und setzen dabei bewusst auf echtes, greifbares Storytelling mit professionellem UGC-Content.

Das bieten wir Dir:
* 500 ‚Ç¨ Pauschalgage
* Teleprompter + eingespielte Crew vor Ort
* Styling & Text-Input durch uns (kein Kost√ºm notwendig, clean/professionell reicht)
* Reelf√§hige Referenz f√ºr Deine Mappe
* Zusammenarbeit mit erfahrenem Videoteam in lockerer, produktiver Atmosph√§re

Bewerbung:

Bitte sende uns bis asap Deine Bewerbung mit:
* 2‚Äì3 aktuellen Bildern oder Showreel
* Kurzprofil (Name, Alter, Standort)
* Optional: Link zu Instagram / Agenturseite / Eigenen Reels
* Betreff: ‚ÄûUGC-Videodreh LEIPZIG ‚Äì Vorname Nachname‚Äú

Bewerbung bitte per WhatsApp an: +49 172 7042469

(Phillip Kirillov - IMMO4.0 GmbH)

Hinweis:

Die finalen Produktionen erscheinen im Rahmen einer Online-Marketingkampagne f√ºr den Bereich Kapitalanlage-Immobilien. Seri√∂s, hochwertig, glaubw√ºrdig.

items.text:
F√ºr meinen historisch-romantischen Kurzfilm (1‚Äì3 Minuten) suche ich eine Schauspielpartnerin (25‚Äì30 Jahre) aus Ulm oder Umgebung.

√úber das Projekt:
Es handelt sich um ein Herzensprojekt, nicht bezahlt, daf√ºr mit viel Leidenschaft. Wir drehen eine Szene im Stil klassischer Historienromanzen ‚Äì Spaziergang, Dialoge voller Tiefe, ein erster Kuss und eine leidenschaftliche Kaminszene.

Wichtig:

Keine Scheu oder Scham vor einem Kuss und einer leidenschaftlichen Szene (√§sthetisch, stilvoll, keine Nacktheit).

Du musst keine ausgebildete Schauspielerin sein ‚Äì entscheidend ist deine Spielfreude, Leidenschaft und der Mut, dich auf die Rolle einzulassen.

Wir bieten:

Ein kleines, motiviertes Team

Eine professionelle Umsetzung mit viel Herzblut

Material f√ºr dein Showreel

Eine intensive Erfahrung voller Romantik und Leidenschaft

üì© Wenn du Lust hast, Teil dieses Projekts zu werden, melde dich bitte mit einer kurzen Nachricht und Foto.

‚ú® Lass uns gemeinsam eine Szene erschaffen, die Romantik und Leidenschaft lebendig macht! ‚ú®

Keine Scheu oder Scham vor einem Kuss und einer leidenschaftlichen Szene (√§sthetisch, stilvoll, keine Nacktheit).

Du musst keine ausgebildete Schauspielerin sein ‚Äì entscheidend ist deine Spielfreude, Leidenschaft und der Mut, dich auf die Rolle einzulassen.

Wir bieten:

Ein kleines, motiviertes Team

Eine professionelle Umsetzung mit viel Herzblut

Material f√ºr dein Showreel

Eine intensive Erfahrung voller Romantik und Leidenschaft

üì© Wenn du Lust hast, Teil dieses Projekts zu werden, melde dich bitte mit einer kurzen Nachricht und Foto.

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

üé≠ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì New Australian Play in London** üé≠

We are casting **four roles** for an exciting new Australian play, *The Beat of the Bronzewing*, which will have a **showcase reading at the Hen & Chickens Theatre, Islington, on November 12th**.

üå™Ô∏è **About the Play:**
When Peggy shows up at Lorraine‚Äôs shack in dead-end tropical Australia, she brings an irresistible offer: a one-way ticket out of there. But with a cyclone looming and old wounds resurfacing, can Lorraine be convinced she has nothing to lose?

‚ú® Longlisted for the **Theatre 503 International Playwriting Award 2025**, *The Beat of the Bronzewing* explores the lives of three women in remote Australia, grappling with toxic femininity, domestic abuse, and rural isolation. Set against an evocative tropical landscape, the play is a gripping story of friendship, fear, and survival.

üë©‚Äçüé§ **The Team**
‚úçÔ∏è Writer & Producer: Charlotte Churcher
üé¨ Director: Chloe Cattin
ü§ù In partnership with the Australian Women‚Äôs Club London

üìÖ **Key Dates**
* **Auditions:** October 8th (12‚Äì5pm) at the Old Red Lion Theatre, Angel, Islington (alternative arrangements available if needed)
* **Rehearsals:** Sunday 9th November (10am‚Äì6pm) & Wednesday 12th November (from 2:30pm)
* **Showcase:** Tuesday 12th November at Hen & Chickens Theatre

üí∑ This is a **volunteer opportunity** with a ¬£50 contribution towards expenses.

üëâ To apply, please complete the form in full.
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSch7cgoIcL_f8KVARDySxKb7eM4Q2gpUXLmmDLPhppJCDDR-w/viewform

Scottish accent preferred, not essential Retregnka Rehearsals on 9th November (10am (10am-6pm) and 12th November (2:30 to 7pm). Please submit via the Google form link provided. This sa volunteer opportunity. All actors will be given ¬£50 pounds for expenses.'

*Join us at the Hive Connect: Monthly Creative Networking/Gathering*

Join us on Sunday 28th September at Wolverhampton Art Gallery, between 1-4pm for an inspiring session of short film screenings, creative talks, networking, workshops, games and collaboration.

Looking to cast for cruises, hotels, resorts, amusement parks, or festivals? Here‚Äôs the fastest way to run turnkey auditions with our agency. üëâBook your audition:
https://risingstars-talents.com/entertainment-casting-agency-turnkey-auditions/?utm_source=reg-FB-RS-rstM

‚úÖHOW IT WORKS:
1. Send your brief: roles, show format, dates, budget, location(s) or remote.
2. Choose audition format: Online (Zoom/Teams), On-site, or Hybrid.
3. We prep everything: casting panel, schedule, tech host, brief pack.
4. Audition day: we host, time-stamp and record every take.
5. Shortlist in 24‚Äì72h: links, notes, availability, indicative rates.
6. Finalize & onboard: callbacks, offers, contracts, visas, travel & riders.

27 years ¬∑ 49,000+ talents ¬∑ 47 countries ¬∑ 27 managers
The Best Talents for The Best Shows.

items.text:
Casting Call (Non-Union) Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of a client in a simulated therapy session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. The sessions are generally improvised with some prompts or loose scripting.

All ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are welcome. We are also very interested in filming with queer couples, interracial couples, or polycules.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are September 23 through 26, but more will occur in the future so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is 60 cad, duration: 1 hour

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again.

Tickets are now available for our upcoming Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event, taking place on Sunday, October 26th.

This is a powerful opportunity to connect with a talented cast and crew who can help bring your next project to life.

 

Networking is essential for advancing your career in the industry, and Marble Academy for Drama and Management has proudly facilitated these events for years. With over 90 attendees, our June gathering was a tremendous success, and we are determined to build on that momentum.

This afternoon we had the pleasure of entertaining a full house for Pettswood WI with our performance of Mr Macabre's Inn. 

The WI is a unique organisation shaped by its members. In 1915, it  set out to give women a voice and to be a force for good in the community. Today, it is the largest women‚Äôs organisation in the UK priding itself on being a trusted place for all women of all generations, to share experiences and learn from each other.

It's 1840, Victorian England‚Ä¶ Deep in the heart of the Kent countryside, not far from the hop farm and the coastline is a secluded little hamlet, with a very old established Inn‚Ä¶
Has Mr. Macabre the Innkeeper being pulling more than pints?
What's the secret ingredient in Mrs. Macabre's popular pies?
Does Tomjon Jones poach more than eggs?

Watch the events unfold and see if you can solve the Murder at Macabre‚Äôs Inn?

Next week we are performing Mr Macabre's Inn on Friday for Sheppey 92.5FM and on Saturday in Boughton Monchelsea, Maidstone.

CASTING CALL

We‚Äôre looking for a female actor to join us this December for our RAPUNZEL pantomime (school tour). 

We‚Äôre casting either of the following parts, with our existing performer playing the opposite role. 

- Rapunzel (lead)
- Gothel (villain)

Last year was our best selling tour - but we hope to beat that this year! Because it‚Äôs schools, the shows are weekday mornings and early afternoons, so you‚Äôll have your evenings and weekends free. The performances are in the Norfolk, Suffolk and Cambridge area. 

We‚Äôre currently offering a minimum of ¬£870 - which will go up as we get more bookings in + travel expenses. 
The tour spans from 1st - 19th December 2025. 
Aiming to start weekly rehearsals asap - in Hunstanton (PE36). These are unpaid but we keep them as flexible as possible.

This will be our thirteenth panto tour, and we‚Äôve built up a good name in the area, with schools booking us year after year (even before we announce the title!) We pride ourselves on being a warm, friendly, but professional company.

If interested, please get in touch for further details - either by a PM on here, or via email - purple-dreams@hotmail.co.uk - I‚Äôm looking forward to hearing from (some of) you üôÇ

Many thanks
Tobias Nicholls
Creative Director 
Purple Dreams Productions

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

items.text:
LOOKING FOR 2 MEN (preferably BASS or BARITONE), 1 WOMAN (preferably ALTO) who can dance and have the ability to harmonize, for our upcoming Holiday Show. 

Ensemble Stage is a professional theater located in Banner Elk, NC which is situated in the Blue Ridge Mtns. in western North Carolina. Our facility consists of over 8000 sq. ft. which includes a 99-seat performance auditorium.

About 90 total hours (rehearsals + performances), no two-show days, no 10-out-of-12's, no more than 3 performances per week (7 total performances). 

contract runs 11/14 thru 12/20.  Fyi- we have no rehearsals Wednesday thru Saturday of Thanksgiving week so you have an opportunity to go be with family if you choose. 

Pay is $260 per week for five weeks (comes to around $14 per hour of actual rehearsal and performance time). Housing is fully provided(includes full kitchen, washer/dryer, wifi, free parking, individual bedroom, no more than two share a bathroom (but usually private) , etc.  Also, no smoking, and no pets (or service animals) are allowed in any housing. 

Round-trip travel reimbursed at $0.25 per mile

Finally,since we are located in the mountains, and since Ensemble Stage does not have a "company car" available for use, having your own vehicle while here is pretty much a necessity. There really is no such thing as walking to the store or to the theatre.

If interested please respond to info@ensemblestage.com, subject- CMAS AUDITIONS. I will then send you details and parameters for you to prepare a video callback audition to be submitted.

About 90 total hours (rehearsals + performances), no two-show days, no 10-out-of-12's, no more than 3 performances per week (7 total performances). 

contract runs 11/14 thru 12/20.  Fyi- we have no rehearsals Wednesday thru Saturday of Thanksgiving week so you have an opportunity to go be with family if you choose. 

Pay is $260 per week for five weeks (comes to around $14 per hour of actual rehearsal and performance time). Housing is fully provided(includes full kitchen, washer/dryer, wifi, free parking, individual bedroom, no more than two share a bathroom (but usually private) , etc.  Also, no smoking, and no pets (or service animals) are allowed in any housing. 

Round-trip travel reimbursed at $0.25 per mile

Finally,since we are located in the mountains, and since Ensemble Stage does not have a "company car" available for use, having your own vehicle while here is pretty much a necessity. There really is no such thing as walking to the store or to the theatre.

If interested please respond to info@ensemblestage.com, subject- CMAS AUDITIONS. I will then send you details and parameters for you to prepare a video callback audition to be submitted.
items.title: LOOKING FOR 2 MEN (preferably BASS or BARITONE), 1 WOMAN (preferably ALTO) who can dance and have the ability to harmonize, for our upcoming Holiday Show.

items.text:
Thank you so much for welcoming me to your group!  

I'm a NYC and NJ native, now living in Florida, pursuing acting work to support my film project.  I have significant experience in films.  Supported directors and producers.  I had 5 years as an extra for feature films such as El Cantante, Be Kind/Rewind, and traveled to audition for theatre and short films. Beyond acting, I'm an editor, photographer, and former Spectrum Television production intern with five years of hands-on experience with equipment, and in 2019 created my first show in Western Connecticut, Channel 192, "Spoken Voices."  A passionate advocate against domestic violence. I bring dedication, creativity, and authenticity to every role, and you can find me on FaceBook, "Maribel Brooks" for future auditioning!

Calling all my filmie friends!!  This Wednesday is our next meetup... come on down, share what you're working on, what you want to work on and talk film.  Its so fun to be around people who share your passions... This includes actors, crew, or people love to watch films and want to talk about them.  
Register here:
https://www.wifvne.org/event-6307681

Hi Everyone!

Sharing from Bryar Casting, in case you haven‚Äôt heard yet, **The Reality Directory** is a fresh casting platform connecting real people with amazing opportunities in reality TV, documentaries, commercials looking for everyday folks with incredible stories!

Whether you‚Äôre outgoing, quirky, or just your authentic self, this is your chance to be discovered by casting producers looking for people just like you.

Memberships start at $14.99/month. If you‚Äôre keen to join or want to learn more, check it out here: www.therealitydirectory.com

And to help you get started, DM us @therealitydirectory with the code **FOUND** for an exclusive discount!

Got questions? Feel free to reach out at casting@therealitydirectory.com or tag friends who might be interested ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to welcome you to the community!

Hello all, this is another post for a different student film happening on Auraria Campus. I am not involved in this one, I am posting to this group for the producer since he is not on Facebook. So if you are interested in this one please contact the producer. 

Producer- Brennan Jones bjones89@msudenver.edu 

Production Title- The Cost of Greed 

Production Dates- Exact dates are not set but filming will be in October 

Logline- Peter and Henry are sent on a treasure hunt to a house that is believed to be abandoned. Where they then discover it's not a treasure hunt after all and they must face their greed. Either take the treasure or leave empty handed. 

Peter (19-25) Male 

Peter has a moral compass that he deals with during this film. He wants to do the right thing and in the end that pays off for him. 

Henry (19-25) Male 

Henry is a billionaire with no need for more money, however that does not stop him from thinking he needs more. He is corrupt and in the end karma gets to him. 

Audition Dates- September 18th-September 29th

Audition Location- Email-Self Tape

This is a student film for a final project therefore this film is non paid and non union.

Contact Email- bjones89@msudenver.edu 

Must contact the producer to be consider for the role. Once you contact Brennan he will send you the audition material.

items.text:
Hello, we are currently casting for a student film on Auraria Campus! 

Producers- Isabella Coronado & Alanagh Finken 

Production Title- Normal Activity 

Production Dates- We don't have exact dates yet but we do know that we are filming in October. 

Logline- A mocumentary following a college's ghost hunting group as they prepare to explore a haunted local brewery's basement where a spirit has resided for the past thirty years. 

Alex (19-25) Male 

Alex is the leader of the ghost hunting group, he is very enthusiastic. He is clearly the one that is most devoted to this group. 

Chelsea (19-25) Female 

Chelsea is your typical girly girl likes being on camera but does not care about the club she is in. She is pretending to so that the club can get funding for the "haunted (not haunted) hot springs". 

Tommy (19-25) Male 

Tommy is very clearly apart of the club because he has eyes for Chelsea, he could not care less otherwise. 

Vera (19-25) Female 

Vera is Alex's sister and is only there because Alex believes they needed a fourth member and basically bribed Vera to join by saying she could borrow his car whenever she wants. 

Gary (45-55) Male 

Gary is the nightwatchmen for the brewery basement. He is very encouraging to Alex with his ghost hunting group. However that encouragement is not for reasons you think, Gary has a secret. 

Documentarian (20-30) Male, Female, Non Binary 

The documentarian is not really shown on camera, however they play a very important role. They are the voice we hear throughout the film asking questions to our characters, and making sarcastic and humorous remarks because they like everyone except Alex, thinks this club is utterly ridicules. 

Audition Dates- September 18th-September 29th 

Audition Location- Email-Self Tape 

This is a student film for a final project therefore this film is non paid and non union. 

**Contact Email- afinken1@msudenver.edu | icoronad@msudenver.edu **

**You must email both producers. Email the producers about your interest in the role and then we will send you the audition piece for your self tape. You must email to be considered, Facebook Messages does not count. **

Casting Call ‚Äì Voice Actors (Ul√∏nnet)

Hej alle,

Vi er et hold fra Masterclass p√• Potemkin ‚Äì Den Jyske Filmskole, som er i postproduktion p√• et sp√¶ndende projekt. Derfor s√∏ger vi nu stemmeskuespillere til to roller.

Logline:

En h√•befuld, men overset filminstrukt√∏r f√•r chancen i en branche styret af sequels og profit ‚Äì og m√• v√¶lge mellem at g√• p√• kompromis med sine v√¶rdier eller med sin karriere.

Vi s√∏ger:

 ‚Ä¢ Kvindestemme ‚Äì til at udlevere en Robertpris (kort ceremoniel replik - t√¶nk "And the Oscar goes to..."). Alder er underordnet.

 ‚Ä¢ Mandestemme ‚Äì til rollen som producer (kort telefondialogscene). Alder underordnet, da det er stemmen vi s√∏ger, men vi s√∏ger i omfanget af 25-39 √•r. 

Praktisk:

 ‚Ä¢ Projektet er ul√∏nnet, men alle medvirkende bliver krediteret i filmen.
        ‚Ä¢ Lydoptagelsen vil foreg√• i Potemkins lydstudie p√• Fredens Torv 3A, Aarhus C 8000.

Er du interesseret? Send mig en mail p√• simonthomaslange@gmail.com med en kort besked, eventuelt som lydoptaglese, s√• f√•r du flere detaljer :)

Vi gl√¶der os til at h√∏re fra dig!

I AM Productions is Now Casting for the Hit Stage Play "Sleeping with the Enemy" In Tallahassee & Leesburg FL 

We Need: Actors, Background Singers, Dancers, & Musicians
Paid: Commission Based 

Female Roles
1. Melody: Lead, Ability to Sing 
2. Michelle: Ability to Sing, Girl Next-door
3. Tiffany: Loud, Ghetto, Funny
4. Jerlma: Ability to Sing, Funny, Cool Grandma
5. Max: Crazy, Alter Ego

Male Roles
1. Dr. Love: Ability to Sing, Handsome, Male Lead
2. Dr. Damion: Swagger, Smooth, Ability to sing (optional)
3. Mr. Eugene: Neighborhood Crackhead
4. Pastor Perry: Funny, Loud, Extra
5. Tyrone: Distinct Voice, Funny

More info 352-231-1198 or email IAMProductions352@gmail.com

*Video auditions are accepted
Submit Headshot, Resume, Monologue video and singing video (if role requires)

items.text:
Hello, I'm Sunita and something to know about me is that I became full time actor only in 2022 after successful decades as a professor and culture worker. For the last third of my earthly existence I want to help enflesh meaningful inspiring stories with my creative skills primarily as an actor currently, but also as a writer, producer, director. I am also known as Suni M! Yes, with an exclamation point! 

Join me for screening of the short film NANI this Thursday, September 25 at the AMC 16 in Burbank. YES!

items.title: Let's welcome our new members!

items.text:
Hi all . Hope your all well. 

I haven‚Äôt posted much in groups in the last few years . I am a multi award winning actor . I am also an internationally trained acting coach and the owner of The Foundry Acting Studio. 
After my little girl almost died I took several years away from acting and instead spent the time to create a curriculum that would match up to some of the biggest schools in the U.K. and USA ‚Ä¶. I‚Äôm glad to say that I have achieved that. We exceeded spotlights requirements by almost three times and got our spotlight approval . We are also the only studio in the U.K. that‚Äôs spotlight approved and SAG recognised with more to come . 

While taking a break from pushing my acting career I spent all my time and money building this curriculum and making movies to help unseen actors . I refused to return to America and instead stayed here to help others. I am happy to say that we are now one of the only studios that make our own industry standard feature films and cast from our students. So training with us guarantees work and spotlight registration. 

I‚Äôve also became a writer over the 6 years I took off from acting and sold scripts to Lionsgate directors . I‚Äôve became great friends with many directors , producers etc who have films on Netflix , through Lionsgate and Warner Bros as well as many others and have made connections with casting directors , agents etc throughout Ireland , uk and America . 

So if your looking an acting class you can trust . Look no further . We don‚Äôt hold massive classes either as no actor should ever become a ¬£ sign. I keep my classes to a level where every actor gets the attention they deserve . 

I‚Äôve actors move from some of the biggest schools in the north to join me as in their previous classes they have felt rushed , not challenged and have said they learnt more with me in a matter of weeks compared to years of doing the same thing over and over again elsewhere . 

I get it . New acting schools , even new headshots specialists , new showreel makers . We all get a considerable amount of doubt . But you do not get more legitimate than being spotlight approved and SAG recognised. 
We also are an extremely supportive group of people , all our students help each other grow and look for work while being there to support them from auditions to being on set. Like a proper family. 

The industry should be a kind and supportive network . I‚Äôve noticed in the last few years just keeping an eye here and there on groups that a lot of people are very rude , ignorant , and just attack people for no reason or simply for trying to peruse their career or ask for help. This is not how it should be and anyone doing so just shows everyone why they will never be cast . We are looking , supportive , kind and driven actors . If that‚Äôs you . 

Give our page a follow and a message and come and try out a class . 

Hope to see some of you soon and hope you all have a wonderful week. Keep pushing for your dreams and never let anyone tell you , you can‚Äôt do it . 

Much love and respect to all . 

Ps. I‚Äôm making a film to showcase as many actors as I can . So if you wish to shoot a one minute monologue and send to myself . I will be attaching as many actors as possible to the film to show your abilities . All you have to do is record at home and imagine it‚Äôs for the last audition you will ever do. If you only ever had one audition left . What would you do ? Hoe would you show your talent. Then I will be pushing this everywhere to show off as many actors as possible. This has gained massive momentum and I‚Äôm offering to help as many as I can . 

Thank you

message.text:
Have you always wanted to act but didn‚Äôt know where to start?
At The Foundry Acting Studio, we make it simple.

We‚Äôre Spotlight approved and SAG-AFTRA recognised, which means our training meets the highest professional standard. Our students don‚Äôt just learn in class‚Ä¶ they perform on set, in real films we create right here at the school.

You‚Äôll be guided by an internationally trained coach, alongside a supportive group of actors just like you. Don‚Äôt just take our word for it, our testimonials show real students growing in confidence every single week.

Whether you dream of the stage, the screen, or simply finding your voice, this is where it starts.

Your first class is free‚Ä¶. come see for yourself why The Foundry is different.
Click Join Now and take your first step into acting today.‚Äù

Online , in person and one to one classes available in several locations

items.summary:
Hi all . Hope your all well. 

I haven‚Äôt posted much in groups in the last few years . I am a multi award winning actor . I am also an internationally trained acting coach and the owner of The Foundry Acting Studio. 
After my little girl almost died I took several years away from acting and instead spent the time to create a curriculum that would match up to some of the biggest schools in the U.K. and USA ‚Ä¶. I‚Äôm glad to say that I have achieved that. We exceeded spotlights requirements by almost three times and got our spotlight approval . We are also the only studio in the U.K. that‚Äôs spotlight approved and SAG recognised with more to come . 

While taking a break from pushing my acting career I spent all my time and money building this curriculum and making movies to help unseen actors . I refused to return to America and instead stayed here to help others. I am happy to say that we are now one of the only studios that make our own industry standard feature films and cast from our students. So training with us guarantees work and spotlight registration. 

I‚Äôve also became a writer over the 6 years I took off from acting and sold scripts to Lionsgate directors . I‚Äôve became great friends with many directors , producers etc who have films on Netflix , through Lionsgate and Warner Bros as well as many others and have made connections with casting directors , agents etc throughout Ireland , uk and America . 

So if your looking an acting class you can trust . Look no further . We don‚Äôt hold massive classes either as no actor should ever become a ¬£ sign. I keep my classes to a level where every actor gets the attention they deserve . 

I‚Äôve actors move from some of the biggest schools in the north to join me as in their previous classes they have felt rushed , not challenged and have said they learnt more with me in a matter of weeks compared to years of doing the same thing over and over again elsewhere . 

I get it . New acting schools , even new headshots specialists , new showreel makers . We all get a considerable amount of doubt . But you do not get more legitimate than being spotlight approved and SAG recognised. 
We also are an extremely supportive group of people , all our students help each other grow and look for work while being there to support them from auditions to being on set. Like a proper family. 

The industry should be a kind and supportive network . I‚Äôve noticed in the last few years just keeping an eye here and there on groups that a lot of people are very rude , ignorant , and just attack people for no reason or simply for trying to peruse their career or ask for help. This is not how it should be and anyone doing so just shows everyone why they will never be cast . We are looking , supportive , kind and driven actors . If that‚Äôs you . 

Give our page a follow and a message and come and try out a class . 

Hope to see some of you soon and hope you all have a wonderful week. Keep pushing for your dreams and never let anyone tell you , you can‚Äôt do it . 

Much love and respect to all . 

Ps. I‚Äôm making a film to showcase as many actors as I can . So if you wish to shoot a one minute monologue and send to myself . I will be attaching as many actors as possible to the film to show your abilities . All you have to do is record at home and imagine it‚Äôs for the last audition you will ever do. If you only ever had one audition left . What would you do ? Hoe would you show your talent. Then I will be pushing this everywhere to show off as many actors as possible. This has gained massive momentum and I‚Äôm offering to help as many as I can . 

Thank you

Hey everyone! I‚Äôm so excited to announce my upcoming short film, Goodbye Luca. This project means so much to me, and I‚Äôd love your help in making it a reality.

We‚Äôre currently casting actors aged 16‚Äì19. No experience needed! This is a great opportunity to be part of a creative project and gain on-set experience.

Location: London
Shoot Dates: 29th Oct & 1st Nov 2025
Deadline: 10th Oct, 5pm BST
Unpaid, but food and drinks will be provided.

Attached below is the link to apply. 

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSexuc0GX9MLusbcqnEKP1sGieziTs7BOka5HMIgziy2vOhHvg/viewform?usp=dialog

Can't wait to see all of your auditions. Thanks, Aliza.

items.summary:
Hey everyone! I‚Äôm so excited to announce my upcoming short film, Goodbye Luca. This project means so much to me, and I‚Äôd love your help in making it a reality.

We‚Äôre currently casting actors aged 16‚Äì19. No experience needed! This is a great opportunity to be part of a creative project and gain on-set experience.

Location: London
Shoot Dates: 29th Oct & 1st Nov 2025
Deadline: 10th Oct, 5pm BST
Unpaid, but food and drinks will be provided.

Attached below is the link to apply. 

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSexuc0GX9MLusbcqnEKP1sGieziTs7BOka5HMIgziy2vOhHvg/viewform?usp=dialog

Can't wait to see all of your auditions. Thanks, Aliza.
items.title: Hey everyone! I‚Äôm so excited to announce my upcoming short film, Goodbye Luca. This project means so much to me, and I‚Äôd love your help in making it a reality.

items.text:
Hi all . Hope your all well. 

I haven‚Äôt posted much in groups in the last few years . I am a multi award winning actor . I am also an internationally trained acting coach and the owner of The Foundry Acting Studio. 
After my little girl almost died I took several years away from acting and instead spent the time to create a curriculum that would match up to some of the biggest schools in the U.K. and USA ‚Ä¶. I‚Äôm glad to say that I have achieved that. We exceeded spotlights requirements by almost three times and got our spotlight approval . We are also the only studio in the U.K. that‚Äôs spotlight approved and SAG recognised with more to come . 

While taking a break from pushing my acting career I spent all my time and money building this curriculum and making movies to help unseen actors . I refused to return to America and instead stayed here to help others. I am happy to say that we are now one of the only studios that make our own industry standard feature films and cast from our students. So training with us guarantees work and spotlight registration. 

I‚Äôve also became a writer over the 6 years I took off from acting and sold scripts to Lionsgate directors . I‚Äôve became great friends with many directors , producers etc who have films on Netflix , through Lionsgate and Warner Bros as well as many others and have made connections with casting directors , agents etc throughout Ireland , uk and America . 

So if your looking an acting class you can trust . Look no further . We don‚Äôt hold massive classes either as no actor should ever become a ¬£ sign. I keep my classes to a level where every actor gets the attention they deserve . 

I‚Äôve actors move from some of the biggest schools in the north to join me as in their previous classes they have felt rushed , not challenged and have said they learnt more with me in a matter of weeks compared to years of doing the same thing over and over again elsewhere . 

I get it . New acting schools , even new headshots specialists , new showreel makers . We all get a considerable amount of doubt . But you do not get more legitimate than being spotlight approved and SAG recognised. 
We also are an extremely supportive group of people , all our students help each other grow and look for work while being there to support them from auditions to being on set. Like a proper family. 

The industry should be a kind and supportive network . I‚Äôve noticed in the last few years just keeping an eye here and there on groups that a lot of people are very rude , ignorant , and just attack people for no reason or simply for trying to peruse their career or ask for help. This is not how it should be and anyone doing so just shows everyone why they will never be cast . We are looking , supportive , kind and driven actors . If that‚Äôs you . 

Give our page a follow and a message and come and try out a class . 

Hope to see some of you soon and hope you all have a wonderful week. Keep pushing for your dreams and never let anyone tell you , you can‚Äôt do it . 

Much love and respect to all . 

Ps. I‚Äôm making a film to showcase as many actors as I can . So if you wish to shoot a one minute monologue and send to myself . I will be attaching as many actors as possible to the film to show your abilities . All you have to do is record at home and imagine it‚Äôs for the last audition you will ever do. If you only ever had one audition left . What would you do ? Hoe would you show your talent. Then I will be pushing this everywhere to show off as many actors as possible. This has gained massive momentum and I‚Äôm offering to help as many as I can . 

Thank you

message.text:
Have you always wanted to act but didn‚Äôt know where to start?
At The Foundry Acting Studio, we make it simple.

We‚Äôre Spotlight approved and SAG-AFTRA recognised, which means our training meets the highest professional standard. Our students don‚Äôt just learn in class‚Ä¶ they perform on set, in real films we create right here at the school.

You‚Äôll be guided by an internationally trained coach, alongside a supportive group of actors just like you. Don‚Äôt just take our word for it, our testimonials show real students growing in confidence every single week.

Whether you dream of the stage, the screen, or simply finding your voice, this is where it starts.

Your first class is free‚Ä¶. come see for yourself why The Foundry is different.
Click Join Now and take your first step into acting today.‚Äù

Online , in person and one to one classes available in several locations

items.summary:
Hi all . Hope your all well. 

I haven‚Äôt posted much in groups in the last few years . I am a multi award winning actor . I am also an internationally trained acting coach and the owner of The Foundry Acting Studio. 
After my little girl almost died I took several years away from acting and instead spent the time to create a curriculum that would match up to some of the biggest schools in the U.K. and USA ‚Ä¶. I‚Äôm glad to say that I have achieved that. We exceeded spotlights requirements by almost three times and got our spotlight approval . We are also the only studio in the U.K. that‚Äôs spotlight approved and SAG recognised with more to come . 

While taking a break from pushing my acting career I spent all my time and money building this curriculum and making movies to help unseen actors . I refused to return to America and instead stayed here to help others. I am happy to say that we are now one of the only studios that make our own industry standard feature films and cast from our students. So training with us guarantees work and spotlight registration. 

I‚Äôve also became a writer over the 6 years I took off from acting and sold scripts to Lionsgate directors . I‚Äôve became great friends with many directors , producers etc who have films on Netflix , through Lionsgate and Warner Bros as well as many others and have made connections with casting directors , agents etc throughout Ireland , uk and America . 

So if your looking an acting class you can trust . Look no further . We don‚Äôt hold massive classes either as no actor should ever become a ¬£ sign. I keep my classes to a level where every actor gets the attention they deserve . 

I‚Äôve actors move from some of the biggest schools in the north to join me as in their previous classes they have felt rushed , not challenged and have said they learnt more with me in a matter of weeks compared to years of doing the same thing over and over again elsewhere . 

I get it . New acting schools , even new headshots specialists , new showreel makers . We all get a considerable amount of doubt . But you do not get more legitimate than being spotlight approved and SAG recognised. 
We also are an extremely supportive group of people , all our students help each other grow and look for work while being there to support them from auditions to being on set. Like a proper family. 

The industry should be a kind and supportive network . I‚Äôve noticed in the last few years just keeping an eye here and there on groups that a lot of people are very rude , ignorant , and just attack people for no reason or simply for trying to peruse their career or ask for help. This is not how it should be and anyone doing so just shows everyone why they will never be cast . We are looking , supportive , kind and driven actors . If that‚Äôs you . 

Give our page a follow and a message and come and try out a class . 

Hope to see some of you soon and hope you all have a wonderful week. Keep pushing for your dreams and never let anyone tell you , you can‚Äôt do it . 

Much love and respect to all . 

Ps. I‚Äôm making a film to showcase as many actors as I can . So if you wish to shoot a one minute monologue and send to myself . I will be attaching as many actors as possible to the film to show your abilities . All you have to do is record at home and imagine it‚Äôs for the last audition you will ever do. If you only ever had one audition left . What would you do ? Hoe would you show your talent. Then I will be pushing this everywhere to show off as many actors as possible. This has gained massive momentum and I‚Äôm offering to help as many as I can . 

Thank you
